column1: (1) - The I/O Grouping column is used to determine the average DC current drawn by I/Os between GNDIO on die and VCCIO connections, or between the last GNDIO/VCCIO in an I/O bank and the end of an I/O bank. The GNDIO/VCCIO substrate pads that determine the I/O grouping are not necessarily connected with a package ball or pin.
(LVDS)* - Supports true LVDS. Other differential signals must be emulated with external resistors.
